PROJECT1: CREATING  OF AZURE VM OVER CONFIGURAING GIT 

Set up VM in Azure with Git installed:
Log in to the Azure Portal.
https://signup.azure.com/signup?offer=ms-azr-0003p&appId=102&ref=&redirectURL=https%3A%2f%2fazure.microsoft.com%2fget-started%2fwelcome-to-azure%3Ficid%3Dacom_payg&l=en-in&srcurl=https%3A%2F%2Fazure.microsoft.com%2Fpricing%2Fpurchase-options%2Fpay-as-you-go
Click on "Create a resource" and search for "Virtual Machine".
Follow the prompts to create a virtual machine, selecting your preferred operating system.
During the setup process, make sure to select "Install Git" or manually install Git after the VM is provisioned.

Clone Repo to the VM:
SSH into your Azure VM.
Navigate to the directory where you want to clone the repository.
Use the git clone command followed by the URL of your Azure Repos repository.
git clone URL of REPO 

Make Changes on the VM:
Use your preferred text editor or IDE to make changes to the code on the VM.

Commit Changes Locally:
After making changes, use git add . to stage your changes.
Then, use git commit -m "Your commit message" to commit your changes locally.

Push Changes to Azure Repos:
Use git push to push your committed changes to Azure Repos.

Create Pull Request from Azure Repos:
Go to your Azure Repos repository in the Azure DevOps portal.
Click on "Pull Requests" and then "New pull request".
Select the appropriate branches for comparison and create the pull request.

Review Changes:
Collaborators can now review your pull request in Azure Repos.
They can provide feedback, suggest modifications, and discuss the changes directly in the pull request.

Address Feedback:
Based on the feedback received, make necessary changes to your code on the VM.
Commit the changes locally and push them to Azure Repos.

Merge PR:
Once the pull request has been approved by the necessary reviewers, you can merge it into the main branch directly from the Azure Repos interface.

Collaborate:
After the changes are merged, team members can pull the latest changes from the main branch, review them, and collaborate as need. 


HERE ARE THE STEP TO COVER ALL THE NECESSARY REQUIRMENT TO MEET THE NEED OF VM .
